  "text": "The pathophysiological pathway connecting COPD to bone loss is unknown. However, numerous characteristics of COPD patients, in addition to the high incidence of corticosteroid use, may contribute to the decreased BMD observed in this patient population. For example, reduced physical activity levels in COPD patients may be important [CITATION_1] , because skeletal underloading is associated with bone loss [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Other characteristics of individuals with COPD associated with bone loss are cigarette smoking, hypercapnia, respiratory acidosis, vitamin D deficiency, and hypogonadism (4, [CITATION_4] .",
